        "text": "I put together two last-minute essays to send to <https:\/\/2026.plateau-workshop.org\/|PLATEAU> back in December. I’ll share them here one-at-a-time.\n\n_*The Blurry Boundaries Between Programming and Direct Use*_\n&gt; While a narrow conception of programming makes it possible to draw sharp lines between “programming” and “direct use”, many of the efforts of the PL + HCI community call for expanded senses of programming that blur these lines. In this paper, we explore these murky boundaries from both sides, exploring situations where programming systems are used for direct use, and situations where direct-use systems take on the characteristic powers of programming. \n<https:\/\/joshuahhh.com\/paper-plateau-2026-blurry\/|HTML version here>\nPDF version attached below\n\nI’d appreciate hearing any feedback, reactions, questions, etc.!",
